title: For Sale:  Mossberg 500 12ga Persuader
postcontent:
This is an older Mossberg 500 -- it was sold as a home defense gun back in its day (late 1990s), but it's called the Persuader today: it's the 12 ga 20" cylinder bore barrel version with a full length 7 round magazine (for a total of 8 shells of the stoutest stuff you care to shoot).  Unlike today's Persuader with black synthetic stock, this one has a wood stock -- and the condition of the stock is very good -- at least 8 or 9 out of 10.  I don't guess I'd swear that it's perfect, but there are really no visible blemishes on it.  It also has the polymer pistol grip that came with it.  I've had the pistol grip on it a few times -- it's a lot of fun to shoot it that way.

My dad bought this gun in the late 1990s from Sports Authority up in Virginia, as a defensive weapon for their RV.  He doesn't remember ever putting any shells through it.  I've owned it for the last few years, and I've probably put 20 shells through it total.  I've cycled it a lot doing practice and such at the house, but few shells were put through it.  It's really in very nice condition...as new as it can get for an uncommon wood-stocked Persuader model like this.

I'm selling (or trading) because the 12 ga is really more than I care to shoot, and my wife isn't comfortable with it at all, so I'm looking for a 20 ga.  If you would like to buy this outright, I'll be glad to sell it to you.  If you have a similar 20 ga (either Mossy 500 or Rem 870) to trade, I'll consider that as well.  I think I would prefer a youth or Bantam size 20 ga, for the slightly shorter stock.  I don't really have a preference on Mossy vs. Rem -- both are good in my experience.

The closest thing to this model today looks to be a Mossberg 500 Special Purpose model 50579.  Link to it on Buds is below.  This is their current 20" 8 shot package that comes with the full stock and the pistol grip.  Again, today's model has synthetic furniture; you cannot buy one with wood like this today.

http://www.budsgunshop.com/catalog/product_info.php/cPath/37_871/products_id/46281/Mossberg+50579+500SP+12+20+CB++8SH+SYN+PGK

I'm also including (but forgot to haul them out for the picture), 95 rounds of Winchester Heavy Target Load shells, 12 rounds of Winchester Dove and Quail shells, and 5 rounds of Remington 9 pellet 00 buck -- 112 rounds of good stuff to put through this thing.

Bud's has the gun listed for $371 cash price, plus FFL, so it's going to be a $400 package by the time you can buy it.  Gander Mountain has it for $450:

http://www.gandermountain.com/modperl/product/details.cgi?pdesc=Mossberg-500-Persuader-Shotgun&i=728986

I'm asking $320 for the gun, plus another 20 bucks for all the shells -- $340 total package.  Please send me a cash or trade offer and I'll consider it.

title: For Sale:  Very Nice 1940 Vz24 Romanian Contract rifle with bayonet
postcontent:
Hello,

I have a very nice looking 1940 Brno Vz24, Romanian Contract rifle and post war bayonet for sale.  The Romanian Contract rifles were made in occupied Brno, Czechoslovakia under the direction of the Germans as aid to Romania to fight the Russians.  A rifle with neat history. The finish on the rifle and stock are VERY good, frankly one of the best I have seen. There are some interesting marks on the stock (acorn?, script letter). The bolt does not match but is a Czech Romanian Contract bolt. The rifling is strong but dark. Many correctly marked Cz parts. There is a fine crack in the wood at the top of the wrist behind the receiver but I don't believe it to be a problem and is repairable. I have never fired this rifle so I can't speak to its accuracy but I will say the action is the smoothest "mauser" action in my collection.

The bayonet is a 1950 dated blade with a 1946 scabbard.

It really is a beautiful rifle I hate to get rid of but I am trying to add some focus to my collection.

I am asking $320 + $30 Shipping. Must ship to C&R or FFL.

Thanks for looking!
